OL,3,C'Things will never be the same again'
OL,4,Cfor family of stabbed pensioner
OL,6,F"These three men were the voice of our
OL,7,Floved one, when he was unable to speak
OL,8,Fout for himself. For this we will
OL,9,Fforever be grateful to them.
OL,11,F"We have watched the whole trial
OL,12,Fintently, and whilst today's guilty
OL,13,Fverdict will not bring back Terence
OL,14,Four beloved husband, father and
OL,15,Fgrandfather, we can take some small
OL,16,Fcomfort in knowing that justice has
OL,17,Fbeen served.
OL,19,F"We would now like the time to grieve
OL,20,Ffor him privately."
